content:
Financial Services Cloud offers several components to visualize groups and relationships in Lightning pages.

This is a Financial Services Cloud managed package feature.

Financial Services Components That Visualize Groups and Relationships
COMPONENT	DESCRIPTION	TYPE
ARC - Financial Services Cloud	Renders the Actionable Relationship Center hierarchy for an account or contact. Use at person and group levels.	Standard
Group Members (Configurable) - Financial Services Cloud	Displays relationship group members, associated information, and task subtypes in a compact grid. To customize the member details displayed, use a custom Account field set. Use at person and group levels.	Custom
Group Members - Financial Services Cloud	Displays relationship group members and age, phone, mobile, email, next and last interaction dates, and task subtypes in a list. Use at person and group levels.	Custom
Related Account - Financial Services Cloud	Displays related accounts for a person or a group. Displays Account Contact Relationships on a person’s page and Account Account Relationships on a group’s page.	Custom
Relationship Group List - Financial Services Cloud	Displays a person’s groups and group members as a related list. Use at the person level. Create and customize field sets to control what fields are displayed.	Custom
Relationship Map - Financial Services Cloud	Displays a visual model of relationships for accounts, contacts, and individuals. Use at person and group levels.	Custom

You can also:

Control Who Sees What on the Relationship Map and in Group Builder based on users’ roles.
Customize Field Sets to affect relationship group and group member information displayed in components.
Set Up Group Member (Configurable) Component to display relationship group members and associated information.
title: Components for Visualizing Groups and Relationships in Financial Services Cloud
